# Integrate Remote Access for AWS environments

This topic describes how to integrate
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
and
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %},
so that
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
policies can be applied to vendors that need to access AWS cloud
environments.

## Overview

Organizations that use
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
to give vendors access to web apps in the
`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.not-free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_C_CyberArk.CompanyName %}
user
portal`</conditionaltext>`{=html}`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_product_vars.SecureAccessSpace %}
space`</conditionaltext>`{=html} can integrate
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
and
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %},
and then create applicable policies to enforce zero standing access for
these vendors.

When
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
policies are created for vendors, they can authenticate to
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
as usual, and select the required AWSÂ web app from the
`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.not-free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_C_CyberArk.CompanyName %}
user
portal`</conditionaltext>`{=html}`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_product_vars.SecureAccessSpace %}
space`</conditionaltext>`{=html}.

To integrate the services, complete the following steps:

1.  `<xref href="#Configur">`{=html}Configure the Identity SSO settings
    in \[%=cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short%\]`</xref>`{=html}

2.  `<xref href="#Set">`{=html}Create a dedicated role in the
    \[%=cc_product_vars.SCA-short%\] tenant`</xref>`{=html}

3.  `<xref href="#Invite">`{=html}Invite the vendors in
    \[%=cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short%\]`</xref>`{=html}

4.  `<xref href="#Configur2">`{=html}Configure the
    \[%=cc_product_vars.SCA-short%\] policy`</xref>`{=html}

## Before you begin

The AWS web app in the
`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.not-free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_C_CyberArk.CompanyName %}
user
portal`</conditionaltext>`{=html}`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_product_vars.SecureAccessSpace %}
space`</conditionaltext>`{=html} (in the
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
tenant) must be configured to use provisioning.

## []{#Configur}Configure the Identity SSO settings in {% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %} {#configure-the-identity-sso-settings-in .step madcap:autonum="Step 1: "}

You must configure
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
to communicate with
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
when a vendor accesses a web app from the
`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.not-free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_C_CyberArk.CompanyName %}
user
portal`</conditionaltext>`{=html}`<conditionaltext madcap:conditions="SCA-conditions.free-trial">`{=html}{% $cc_product_vars.SecureAccessSpace %}
space`</conditionaltext>`{=html}. This configuration is done in the
{% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}
SSO functionality.

For information about how to configure the
{% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}
SSO settings, see the
[{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
docs](/remote-access-standard/latest/en/content/admin/settings-idaptive.htm){alt="Link to [%=cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short%] topic about configuring [%=cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full% SSO settings]"}.

## []{#Set}Create a dedicated role in the {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %} tenant {#create-a-dedicated-role-in-the-tenant .step madcap:autonum="Step 2: "}

You must create a dedicated role in the
{% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}
instance of the
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
tenant that
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
can use to identify your vendors and apply the relevant policies.

After this role is created, use it when inviting any vendor that should
be included in an
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
policy.

For information about how to create a role, see the
[{% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}
docs](/identity-administration/latest/en/content/coreservices/getstarted/userrolesassign.htm?tocpath=Add%20system%20users%20and%20roles%7CAssign%20users%20to%20roles%20and%20manage%20roles%7C_____0#Createanewrole){target="_blank"
alt="Link to heading on how to create a new role in [%=cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full%] docs"}.

## []{#Invite}Invite the vendors in {% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %} {#invite-the-vendors-in .step madcap:autonum="Step 3: "}

When you invite vendors in
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %},
you have to configure several parameters to enable
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
to identify the vendor and apply the relevant policy.

1.  In the [Allowed applications ]{.Emphasis}area, select the [Allow
    access to Identity web applications ]{.Emphasis}option.

2.  in the [User provisioning ]{.Emphasis}area, do the following:

    1.  Select the
        [{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
        will create and manage the user]{.Emphasis} option.

    2.  In the [Role ]{.Emphasis}field, specify the dedicated role that
        you created for this purpose.

For more information about inviting vendors, see the
[\[%=cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short%\]
docs](/remote-access-standard/latest/en/content/admin/invitevendors.htm "Link to topic in [%=cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short%] on how to invite vendors"){target="_blank"
alt="Link to topic in [%=cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short%] on how to invite vendors"}.

## []{#Configur2}Configure the {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %} policy {#configure-the-policy .step madcap:autonum="Step 4: "}

When you configure an
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
policy to include
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}
vendors, ensure that you select the dedicated role that you created in
{% $cc_product_vars.IdentityAdmin-full %}
when you add identities to the policy.
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
uses this role to identify the vendor so it can apply the policy.

For more information about creating
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
policies, see
`<xref href="../DPAforCloud/sca_create-policies-AWS.htm">`{=html}Create
an AWS policy`</xref>`{=html}.

::: note
You can only create policies for vendors that have been invited to
{% $cc_product_vars.RemoteAccess-short %}.
:::
